# Git push and PRs — confirm first

**Never push or open a PR without explicit user approval** in the current conversation.

- **`git push`** (including `-u origin …`): run `cd app; pnpm run qa` first, summarize branch/commits/QA, then ask. Push only after the user confirms.
- **`gh pr create`** (or equivalent): run QA first, summarize title/scope/test plan/QA, then ask. Create the PR only after the user confirms.
- **PR body on PowerShell**: always `gh pr create --body-file path` — never inline `--body "..."` (backticks break markdown). See `docs/AGENT_WORKFLOW.md`.

Do not treat “work is done” or “branch is ready” as permission to push or open a PR.

Full workflow: `docs/AGENT_WORKFLOW.md` and `AGENTS.md` (Conventions).
